<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jury Duty: Jury selection begins today at the Broward County Courthouse in 
Florida in the trial of Charles Freeman, the Ft. 
</P>
<P>
Lauderdale record store owner who was arrested June 8 for selling a copy of the 
Miami rap group 2 Live Crew's sexually explicit "As Nasty as They Wanna Be" 
album. Freeman, 32, drew national attention after he defied police warnings to 
stop selling the rap record, which was declared obscene on June 6 by U.S. 
District Judge Jose Gonzalez in Ft. Lauderdale. If convicted, Freeman faces up 
to one year in jail and a $1,000 fine. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
