<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the Nick of Time: A benefit concert for political candidates who support 
abortion rights -- featuring Bonnie Raitt, Rickie Lee Jones and others -- was 
abruptly canceled after the Veterans Administration said that its Los Angeles 
theater could not host a partisan event. The concert, whose lineup also 
included Robin Williams and Melissa Etheridge, was scheduled for Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The Hollywood Women's Committee, a political action group, hoped to raise 
$200,000 from the invitation-only concert for the campaigns of congressional 
candidates. Margery Tabankin, executive director of the group, said that the 
committee got permission in July to use the V.A.'s Wadsworth Theater from UCLA. 
But UCLA officials said they did not know the purpose of the concert until last 
week. BETH KLEID 
</P>
