<P>
ELDERLY IMMIGRANT DIES IN ESCALATOR ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MIAMI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An elderly Cuban immigrant taking her first steps in the United States was 
crushed to death Sunday in an escalator accident at Miami International 
Airport, police said. 
</P>
<P>
At least five other passengers were injured. 
</P>
<P>
Bertola Agrispina Acosta-Bereda, 75, was killed under the weight of her fellow 
passengers as they fell on an escalator to the U.S. Customs Service and 
Immigration offices, police said. It was not immediately clear whether the 
escalator malfunctioned or if the immigrants' unfamiliarity with the machinery 
prompted the fall, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The immigrants had arrived on a weekly charter flight bringing Cuban immigrants 
to the United States from Havana and exiles home from visits to the island. 
</P>
