<P>
FRENCHMAN SURRENDERS AFTER A BLOODY SIEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unemployed house painter surrendered Sunday after a 24-hour siege during 
which he shot and wounded five policemen and threatened to kill himself and his 
family. 
</P>
<P>
Patrick Moesta, 33, entered the apartment of his estranged wife in suburban 
Paris at midday Saturday. Neighbors called police when they heard an argument. 
Moesta began firing, wounding five officers and a neighbor. An elite police 
unit sealed off the apartment building. Moesta finally surrendered after 
talking with a prosecutor. 
</P>
<P>
His wife, 10-year-old daughter and 8-year-old son were not hurt. 
