<P>
Products for the Up-Tight Commuter: Commuter Products Corp. of Emeryville is 
making things for commuters who are tense from being stuck in stop-and-go 
traffic. 
</P>
<P>
Mabel Yee's firm offers a massaging car seat, stress-reduction tapes, stereo 
headrests and an electronic message board that tells tailgaters to back off. 
Commuter Products also offers gadgets for before or after a commute. Among 
them: an under-the-pillow alarm that shakes a sleeper without disturbing anyone 
else, a multi-pocket folder to organize glove box rubble and a Car Finder that 
turns on the lights and honks the horn of your car from 200 feet way. 
