<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark I. Pinsky and Sonni Efron 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
REUNIFICATION: Germans and German-Americans will be doing a lot of celebrating 
this week, observing the reunification Wednesday of East and West Germany. . . 
. On that day, some members of the Phoenix Club in Anaheim will gather for a 
festive luncheon, while others will join a larger group at the Los Angeles 
Music Center. "It's a fantastic day for us," says club President Hans Klein. On 
Oct. 6, German-American Day, Mayor Walter Momper of West Berlin will address 
the club in Anaheim. Mark I. Pinsky and Sonni Efron 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
