<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark I. Pinsky and Sonni Efron 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SMALL SCREEN: Huntington Beach businessman Mel Mermelstein, above, who 
successfully sued a Torrance-based group that claimed the Holocaust did not 
occur, is coming to the TV screen. A docudrama, "Never Forget," starring Star 
Trek's Leonard Nimoy, is being shot locally and is due on the TNT cable network 
in January. . . . Mermelstein, an Auschwitz survivor who is often consulted on 
the set, says it was "kind of strange" watching himself portrayed. Even 
stranger: He's playing his own father. Mark I. Pinsky and Sonni Efron 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Mel Mermelstein 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
