<P>
GROUP TO BUY TREES, SHRUBS FOR BARE AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 100 trees and shrubs are headed for a bare section of land near the 
east end of Laguna Lake through the efforts of the Tree Society of Orange 
County. 
</P>
<P>
Jack Heninger, executive director of the Tree Society, said that the group, 
together with volunteers who live in the Laguna Lake area, has formed a joint 
committee to plant the trees and shrubs. 
</P>
<P>
Fund raising to buy the greenery is now under way, Heninger said, and the 
planting is scheduled "come rain or shine, at 9 a.m. on Nov. 10." 
</P>
<P>
The site is at the intersection of Hermosa and Lakeside drives, near the east 
end of Laguna Lake. 
</P>
<P>
"Many volunteers are needed to make light work for all and to complete the 
planting by noon (on Nov. 10)," Heninger said. Volunteers can call the Tree 
Society at (714) 449-7170. 
</P>
<P>
Heninger said the trees are being purchased at a discount from a commercial 
nursery. The city of Fullerton has agreed to install water pipe and connectors 
at 100-foot intervals along the bare land so that the trees and shrubs can be 
watered, he added. -- BILL BILLITER 
