<HEADLINE>
<P>
ELEGANT BARGAIN WINS POMONA INVITATIONAL HANDICAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BURGART, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Elegant Bargain scored a one-length victory Sunday over My Sonny Boy in the 
$150,000 Pomona Invitational Handicap at Fairplex Park. 
</P>
<P>
Under a ground-saving ride from leading jockey David Flores, Elegant Bargain 
took the lead on the far turn. 
</P>
<P>
My Sonny Boy, shuffled back slightly into the backstretch, rallied gamely to 
finish four lengths ahead of pace-setting Double Quick. Favored Annual Date 
raced wide and was fifth in the field of 10 older runners. 
</P>
<P>
Elegant Bargain, trained by Bruce Jackson, ran the 1 1/8 miles in 1:48 4/5, 
earned $82,500 and paid $20.60. 
</P>
<P>
A turf specialist, Elegant Bargin was racing on the main track for the first 
time since winning a stakes race at Los Alamitos last year. 
</P>
<P>
Fairplex Notes 
</P>
<P>
Sandys Love Bug scored a neck win over Casady King in the $50,000 Pomona 
Quarter Horse Invitational Handicap at 400 yards. . . . Racing concludes today 
with Something Comfy heading fillies and mares postward in the $34,240 Amanda 
S. Stakes. . . . With two wins Sunday, David Flores has 33 victories this 
season, five shy of Francisco Mena's all-time record. Roger Stein, with six 
victories, tops the trainer standings. Eight conditioners have four wins each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
