<HEADLINE>
<P>
BECKER TAKES FIRST IN WORSA REGATTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHERLEAN DUKE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ann Becker of Capistrano Bay Yacht Club sailed her J35 to victory and first 
place overall in the 11th WORSA (Women's Ocean Racing Sailing Assn.) Regatta 
held Saturday and Sunday in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 women aboard 13 boats, ranging in size from 24 feet to 41 feet, 
competed in the four-race event, which was held in light winds near the Balboa 
Pier. 
</P>
<P>
Second place went to co-skippers Linda Elias and Cheryl Wiebel of Voyagers 
Yacht Club in their Olson 30, Jiffy Too. Elias and Wiebel are former three-time 
overall winners. Third place went to Kathy Pantaosky of Balboa Yacht Club. 
</P>
<P>
In Class B, Ophelia Voda, Long Beach Yacht Club, finished first, and Kathy 
Adamson, Dana Point Yacht Club, was second. Tying for third were Jane Willet, 
Bahia Corinthian Yacht Club, and Nan Snody, Los Angeles Yacht Club. 
</P>
<P>
In the non-spinnaker class, Gail Hine, South Shore Yacht Club, finished first 
and Bonnie Gibson, Wooden Hull Owners' Assn., was second. 
</P>
<P>
The women-only regatta is the biggest event of the year for the big-boat 
sailors, according to WORSA president Shannon Aikman. Races were hosted jointly 
by four Orange County yacht clubs. SHERLEAN DUKE 
</P>
</TEXT>
