<P>
TEEN KILLED IN HIGHLAND PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two gunmen in a car opened fire on a car stopped in the middle of a Highland 
Park street, killing a 16-year-old and wounding four others, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
The confrontation between the two carloads of gang members in the middle of 
Avenue 50 Sunday night was one of five fatal attacks linked to gang activity 
over the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators believe that the Highland Park incident occurred after the two 
cars, one with eight youths inside and the other carrying two, passed each 
other and then stopped when they recognized rivals, Detective Ron Whitt said. 
</P>
<P>
"They started yelling gang slogans and throwing gang signs at each other until 
two (Latino) males left one car and walked over to the other," Whitt said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
