<P>
SWEDISH GROUP TO BUY U.S. FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AmBase Corp. said today it has agreed to sell its Home Insurance Co. property 
and casualty insurance subsidiary to a Swedish-led investment group in a deal 
valued at $970 million. 
</P>
<P>
The buyer, TVH Acquisition Corp., is led by Trygg-Hansa Holding AB, Sweden's 
second-largest insurance company. It includes European financial services and 
real estate investors Vik Brothers International USA Inc., International 
Insurance Advisors Inc. and Donaldson, Lufkin &amp; Jenrette Inc. 
</P>
<P>
AmBase said the purchase price includes a cash payment of $507 million, 
assumption of $178 million in debt and leaving in place $285 million of Home's 
preferred stock. 
</P>
