<HEADLINE>
<P>
2ND ARSON FIRE HITS MD. RACEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAUREL, Md. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A second fire at Freestate Raceway has been classified as arson, the state fire 
marshal said today. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy State Fire Marshal Bob Thomas said the fire early this morning caused 
$30,000 in damage and destroyed a two-story wood building that was used as a 
lounge for jockeys and employees. 
</P>
<P>
An arson fire at the harness track Saturday afternoon heavily damaged the 
grandstand building, Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities were seeking two youngsters who were seen running from the track 
after the first fire. 
</P>
<P>
The race track has been closed for about a year. 
</P>
<P>
The track was closed after it was sold to the Washington-based Cafritz Group, a 
real estate and development firm. Racing dates at the track had been leased to 
Mark Vogel, who is charged in Virginia with cocaine possession. 
</P>
</TEXT>
