<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
MALDEN ADDS STAMP TO PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Karl Malden is joining the panel that recommends subjects for new U.S. 
postage stamps, the U.S. Postal Service announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Malden, president of the academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences, is one of 
five new members chosen for the Citizens' Stamp Advisory Committee. 
</P>
<P>
The group screens the nearly 30,000 letters received annually suggesting stamp 
subjects and makes recommendations to the postmaster general. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to Malden, new committee members are David Lewis Eynon, executive 
vice president of Amichetti, Lewis &amp; Associates, Bryn Mawr, Pa.; Bernard 
Henning Sr., attorney, Chicago; Stephen T. McLin, president, American First 
Financial Corp., San Francisco, and Robert H. Power, general partner, Nut Tree 
Restaurant, Nut Tree, Calif. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Karl Malden 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
