<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLIPBOARD; 
</P>
<P>
CHILD ABUSE REPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Social Services Agency records incidents of child abuse each 
month. The agency reports the number of families involved and children at risk. 
This does not reflect the total number of children who are actual victims of 
abuse, but, rather, the number of children in the household -- the total number 
who are in danger of being abused. 
</P>
<P>
Here's a look at the first eight months of the year (the most recent period for 
which information is available) on a city-by-city basis. The cities are listed 
in terms of rate per thousand residents. 
</P>
