<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Swedish-Led Group Buys Home Insurance: AmBase Corp. of New York announced a 
definitive agreement to sell its Home Insurance Co. unit to an investor group 
headed by Sweden's second-largest insurer for $970 million. 
</P>
<P>
AmBase's board selected the Trygg-Hansa Holdings group's bid over a competing 
offer from a group led by Sequoia Associates. Trygg-Hansa, based in Stockholm, 
is a multiline insurance carrier with annual premium income of about $2.3 
billion and assets of about $15 billion. In approving the sale of Home 
Insurance, the board also authorized management to come up with a plan to 
restructure AmBase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
